      "type": "float",
      "description": "initial frequency value in Hz",
      "default": "0"
    }
  ],
  "flags": [],
  "methods": [],
  "body": "The osc~ object outputs a cosine wave. The frequency input can be either a float or a signal. The right inlet resets the phase with values from 0 to 1 (where '1' is the same as '0' and '0.5' is half the cycle"
